Manuel Pellegrini fails to back Joe Hart as Manchester City goalkeeper's latest blunder leads to Chelsea victory
Manchester City goalkeeper Joe Hart is not backed by manager Manuel Pellegrini following latest blunder against Chelsea at Stamford Bridge
Lack of form: Now Joe Hart's manager Manuel Pellegrini has failed to support him after yet another blunder Photo: AP	By Telegraph Sport, and agencies
10:07AM GMT 28 Oct 2013
Follow Comments
Manchester City manager Manuel Pellegrini refused to publicly back Joe Hart after yet another error from the England goalkeeper saw Chelsea triumph at Stamford Bridge. The City No1 and Matija Nastasic were involved in a mix-up which gifted Fernando Torres a 90th-minute winner. Following the loss, Pellegrini refused to discuss the errors which resulted in Torres' winner or whether Hart's place is under threat from Costel Pantilimon. "I do it privately with the players," Pellegrini said when asked how he would assess Hart's contribution. After defeats at Cardiff and Aston Villa, the Chilean was left to rue the further loss of "stupid points" away from home. "We repeat the story," he said. "We had absolutely the control of the game. We played very, very well in the second half. We didn't have any problem with Chelsea but finally in the last minute we lost. Related Articles
